     		       Central Nave 

room  > Central Nave

printed name: "Central Nave"

description: "You stand in the middle of the columns lining the central nave and look around. Surrounding you are 17 small cells. Most of them are shrouded in darkness and you could barely see inside, but one directly east of you seems to lead out to a bigger chamber. The doorway back to the first transverse chamber is to your west. The ceiling echoes the structure of a sarcophagus. A large statue dominates the center of the room, its scale representative of what could have nly been a god. In front of it, a low altar sits, its surface decorated with scarce items. "

printed name: "statue of Osiris"

Osiris sits on a throne in a mummified form wearing a close-fitting enveloping garment, a divine beard attached to his chin, and the Atef crown flanked by two ostrich feathers, adorned with the uraeus cobra. He holds the royal crook and flail with his arms crossed on his chest. The base of the statue is inscribed with an offering prayer, while the back pillar of the statue is not inscribed. (from the cairo museum, feel free to change) He sure looks put together-- a drastic difference from his current state."
